Changes Made Today
New Feature: State × Segment Portal Mappings
The CMS contracts editor now supports managing which portal ID a customer is routed to based on their state and organization type. E&I and Omnia have been pre-populated with real portal IDs from BDBTools (E&I Virginia [944], E&I Utah [952], Omnia Florida K-12 [1443], Omnia Florida Higher Ed [1445], and more).
Contract Logos
Real logos for E&I, Omnia, Equalis, TIPS, BuyBoard, and PEPPM are now embedded. They appear in the featured contract panel, on contract pages, and in the sidebar contract list on segment pages.
Org Type Dropdown Navigation
The "Choose Organization Type" dropdown now appears on every segment page and functions as navigation — selecting a different org type takes you directly to that segment's page.
Higher Ed Label
The home page tile changed from "College / University" to "Higher Ed" to match the live site.
State Filter on Higher Ed
The Higher Ed segment page now shows the state filter in the sidebar by default.
Sign-Up Card Fix
The sign-up card on segment pages was being cut off. The hero overflow clipping and height have been corrected — the full card is now visible.

